h3cDHCPServer.name: h3cDHCPServer
h3cDHCPServer.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
h3cDHCPServer.description: The MIB module is used for DHCP server.

h3cDHCPServerIPPoolUsage.name: h3cDHCPServerIPPoolUsage
h3cDHCPServerIPPoolUsage.description: Usage factor of DHCP server ip pool.

h3cDHCPServerReqTimes.name: h3cDHCPServerReqTimes
h3cDHCPServerReqTimes.description: Number of requests received by the DHCP server.

h3cDHCPServerReqSuccessTimes.name: h3cDHCPServerReqSuccessTimes
h3cDHCPServerReqSuccessTimes.description: Number of requests success responses sent by the DHCP server.

h3cDHCPServerAvgIpUseThreshold.name: h3cDHCPServerAvgIpUseThreshold
h3cDHCPServerAvgIpUseThreshold.description: Threshold of average IP useage of a DHCP server pool in 5 minutes.

h3cDHCPServerMaxIpUseThreshold.name: h3cDHCPServerMaxIpUseThreshold
h3cDHCPServerMaxIpUseThreshold.description: Threshold of maximum IP useage of a DHCP server pool in 5 minutes.

h3cDHCPServerAllocateThreshold.name: h3cDHCPServerAllocateThreshold
h3cDHCPServerAllocateThreshold.description: Threshold of DHCP server allocated IP address in 5 minutes.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolTable.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolTable
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server global pools.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEntry.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEntry
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting a global pool for the DHCP server.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolRowStatus.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolRowStatus
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable.description: A table containing the configurations of dhcp server global pools.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigEntry.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigEntry
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the network ip or host ip etc. to global pools for DHCP server.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolType.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolType
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolType.description: Type of a DHCP global pool. Any operations of this object will be bound with the operations of h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork, h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr, or h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr. That means any operation of this object alone will be regarded as invalid operation.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork.description: Network ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag to 1.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetworkMask.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetworkMask
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetworkMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(network). The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a network ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.description: Host ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag to 2.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostMask.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostMask
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(host) The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a host ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr.description: Hardware address of a DHCP global pool(host). To delete a configured hardware address, please set h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag to 3.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag.description: Flag of undo operation for h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr.description: Start IP of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured start IP, please set h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr to 0. It takes effect only when h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork is set.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEndAddr.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEndAddr
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEndAddr.description: End ip of a DHCP global pool.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaTable.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaTable
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaTable.description: A table for configuring parameters to DHCP global pools.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaEntry.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaEntry
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for the configurations of parameters of DHCP global pools.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseDay.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseDay
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseDay.description: Number of days of the lease.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseHour.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseHour
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseHour.description: Number of hours of the lease.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseMinute.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseMinute
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseMinute.description: Number of minutes of the lease.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseUnlimited.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseUnlimited
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseUnlimited.description: A flag denoting if the lease of a pool is unlimited.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPStr.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPStr
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPStr.description: String of gateway ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip ip at a time.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPUndo.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPUndo
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPUndo.description: A gateway ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of gateway router.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPStr.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPStr
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPStr.description: String of DNS server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPUndo.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPUndo
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPUndo.description: A DNS server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of DNS server.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNetbiosType.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNetbiosType
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNetbiosType.description: NetBios node type for DHCP clients.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPStr.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPStr
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPStr.description: String of NetBios server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, so a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPUndo.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPUndo
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPUndo.description: A NetBios server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of NetBios server.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPInUseReset.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPInUseReset
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPInUseReset.description: Reset the auto binding ip of the given global pool for DHCP server.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTime.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTime
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTime.description: Number of timeticks of the lease.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP.description: The Primary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client. To delete a configured Primary DNS server IP, please set h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP to 0. It takes effect only when h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork is set.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP.description: The Secondary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client. To delete a configured Secondary DNS server IP, please set h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP to 0. It takes effect only when h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork is set.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseSecond.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseSecond
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseSecond.description: Number of seconds of the lease.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionTable.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionTable
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionTable.description: A table for configuring options to DHCP global pools.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionEntry.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionEntry
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring options to DHCP global pools.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptHexString.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptHexString
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptHexString.description: Hex string of an option. 1st to 16th hex strings, which are 2 bytes, 4 bytes, 6 bytes or 8 bytes, can be configured at most simultaneously. That means the format of each string must be '12', '1234', '123456' or '12345678'.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptIPString.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptIPString
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptIPString.description: Ip string of an option. 1 to 8 ip addresses can be configured at most simultaneously.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptRowStatus.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptRowStatus
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatTable.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatTable
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatTable.description: The statistics of each DHCP address pool.

h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatEntry.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatEntry
h3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatEntry.description: An entry containing the statistics of each DHCP address pool.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPPoolUsage.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPPoolUsage
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPPoolUsage.description: Utilization rate of IP addresses in each DHCP address pool, in percentage.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolReqTimes.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolReqTimes
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolReqTimes.description: Number of request packets received by each DHCP address pool, including the request packets for an extension of the lease.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSuccessTimes.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSuccessTimes
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSuccessTimes.description: Number of positive responses sent by each DHCP address pool, including responses to the request for an extension of the lease.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolDiscoverTimes.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolDiscoverTimes
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolDiscoverTimes.description: Number of discover packets received by each DHCP address pool.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOfferTimes.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOfferTimes
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOfferTimes.description: Number of offer packets sent by each DHCP address pool.

h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolACKTimes.name: h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolACKTimes
h3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolACKTimes.description: Number of ACK packets sent by each DHCP address pool.

h3cDHCPServerAddrExhaust.name: h3cDHCPServerAddrExhaust
h3cDHCPServerAddrExhaust.description: This trap is generated when the device DHCP server address exhaust.

h3cDHCPServerAddrExhaustRecover.name: h3cDHCPServerAddrExhaustRecover
h3cDHCPServerAddrExhaustRecover.description: This trap is generated when the device DHCP server address exhaust recover.

h3cDHCPServerAvgIpUsageOverflow.name: h3cDHCPServerAvgIpUsageOverflow
h3cDHCPServerAvgIpUsageOverflow.description: This trap is generated when the average IP address usage of DHCP server pool in 5 minutes overflows.

h3cDHCPServerMaxIpUsageOverflow.name: h3cDHCPServerMaxIpUsageOverflow
h3cDHCPServerMaxIpUsageOverflow.description: This trap is generated when the maximun IP address usage of DHCP server pool in 5 minutes overflows.

h3cDHCPServerAllocateOverflow.name: h3cDHCPServerAllocateOverflow
h3cDHCPServerAllocateOverflow.description: This trap is generated when the number of DHCP server allocated IP address in 5 minutes overflows.
